The aim of course is learning vocabulary, development of reading and listening skills, making presentations about the topics in the field of medicine.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop the basic terminology by reading and listening to texts in speciality. To develop students' oral and written communication skills in both their field of specialization and general topics at an upper-intermediate level of Estonian.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the course is able to
* recognize and understand medical terms in the context;
* read and find the main idea of a text concerning his / her speciality;
* follow a lecture on his / her speciality 
* find and present relevant information to the colleague (using terms) and to the   patient in the form of a discussion or a presentation;
* deliver academic presentation on medical topics;
* write a summary of a special text;
